  "bodyPreview": "INSTRUCTIONS:\n\n\nKindly fill the form and click the 'Save as PDF' Button.The 'RESET' Button clears all the fields you have filled-in, so you can start over.\nOnce Saved as PDF you will not be able to make changes.\nUpon clicking 'Save as PDF', a PDF copy of your form will be downloaded, which can be printed, emailed or uploaded to another application.\n\nMPC 150 (12/11/20) \nof\npage\nSave as PDF\nReset Form\nCommonwealth of Massachusetts \nThe Trial Court \nProbate and Family Court \nDocket No.\nEstate of:\nLast Name\nFirst Name\nMiddle Name\nDate of Death:\nPETITION FOR INFORMAL\n PROBATE OF WILL\nAPPOINTMENT OF PERSONAL\nPURSUANT TO G.L. c. 190B, § 3-301\nREPRESENTATIVE\nDivision\nBarnstable\nBerkshire\nBristol\nDukes\nEssex\nFranklin\nHampden\nHampshire\nMiddlesex\nNantucket\nNorfolk\nPlymouth\nSuffolk\nWorcester\nAmended Form \nOriginal Form \nInstructions\nLast Name\nMiddle Name\nFirst Name\nThe Petitioner(s) (hereafter \"Petitioner\"), an interested person, makes the following statements:\n1.\nInformation about the Decedent:\nName:\nI.  \nGENERAL INFORMATION\nAge at death\nAlso known as:\nName\nclick to add Alias\nclick to remove\nThe Decedent was domiciled in\n(City/Town)\n(State)\n.\n(Zip)\n(State)\n(City/Town)\n(Apt, Unit, No. etc.)\n(Address)\nStreet Address:\n,\nFORM ALERT: \nA death certificate issued by a public officer is in the possession of the court or accompanies this \nPetition.\n2.\nInformation about the Petitioner:\nLast Name\nName:\nFirst Name\nM.I.\n(Address)\n(City/Town)\n(State)\n(Zip)\n(Apt, Unit, No. etc.)\nMailing Address, if different:\n(Address)\n(City/Town)\n(State)\n(Zip)\n(Apt, Unit, No. etc.)\nThe Petitioner's interest in the estate is as follows (e.g., Personal Representative named in a will, surviving spouse, heir, \nPrimary Phone #: \n devisee, etc. See  G. L. c. 190B, § 1-201(24)):\nEmail:\nclick to add\nclick to remove\n3.\nThis Petition is filed within the time period permitted by law (See G. L. c. 190B, § 3-108).  Three years or less have passed \nsince the Decedent's death, or the following circumstances authorize tardy proceedings (\ninclude statutory reference\n):\nDo not use this form to file a late probate proceeding pursuant to G. L. c. 190B, § 3-108(4).  Use form  \nMPC 161.\nFORM ALERT: \n4.\nVenue for this proceeding is proper in this county because on the date of death, the Decedent:\nwas domiciled in this county.\nwas not domiciled in Massachusetts, but had property located in this county at:\n(Zip)\n(State)\n(City/Town)\n(Apt, Unit, No. etc.)\n(Address)\nMPC 150 (12/11/20) \nof\npage\n5.\nThe Petitioner gave written notice seven (7) days prior to petitioning for informal probate or appointment by sending a \ncopy of this Petition and death certificate by certified mail to Division of Medical Assistance, Estate Recovery Unit, \nP.O. Box 15205, Worcester, MA  01615-0205.\nII. \nPERSONS INTERESTED IN THE ESTATE\n6.\nThe Decedent's surviving spouse, children, heirs at law and devisees (if any), so far as known or ascertainable with \nreasonable diligence by the Petitioner are as stated in form\n \nMPC 162 Surviving Spou"
